:::summary
Latter-day Saint temples are the most sacred buildings in The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints — dedicated houses of the Lord where members who hold current temple recommends receive sacred ordinances essential to eternal life: the endowment, eternal marriage sealings, and proxy ordinances for deceased ancestors. Temples are distinct from ordinary meetinghouses; they are open only to faithful, prepared Church members. As of 2026, over 350 temples are in operation, under construction, or announced worldwide.
:::

